Document: overview_of_debugging_tools
Path: godot/tutorials/scripting/debug/overview_of_debugging_tools.rst
Summary: Explains the Remote scene dock option for inspecting and modifying running project parameters.
Remote in scene dock
When running a game in the editor two options appear at the top of the Scene dock, Remote and Local. While using Remote you can inspect or change the nodes' parameters in the running project. Note: Some editor settings related to debugging can be found inside the Editor Settings, under the Network > Debug and Debugger sections.